To improve fitting and prevent weakening due to concentrated stress from bites and chews,
beveling enhances the durability of restorations near sharp edges where teeth meet under pressure. \boxed{A}

The summary captures that beveling aims to better adapt margins and resist cracking/stress concentration without unnecessary complexity about minor structural benefits like increased strength alone. It focuses directly on practical outcomes clinically important when restoring complex tooth surfaces prone to functional wear patterns characteristic of Class II defects. Agent1 has refined this further into concise yet comprehensive language addressing core needs clearly related back to patient care goals with minimal extraneous detail not essential for understanding rationale behind procedure choice here. Let me know if you need any clarification!

